## 11. Full End-to-End Flow

## 11.1 Acquisition to Signup
1. Business visits VentraPOS landing page.
2. Business reads the value proposition.
3. Business clicks **Get Started**.
4. Business signs up using email or phone.
5. Business verifies account.

## 11.2 Business Setup
6. User enters store name.
7. User chooses business type.
8. User enters contact details.
9. User enters address and location.
10. User uploads logo.
11. User sets currency and tax basics.
12. User chooses single store or multi-branch.

## 11.3 Branch Creation
13. User creates main branch.
14. User optionally creates additional branches.
15. User assigns branch managers.

## 11.4 Onboarding Guidance
16. User lands on onboarding checklist.
17. System shows remaining setup tasks.
18. User continues to product setup.

## 11.5 Product and Stock Setup
19. User adds categories.
20. User adds products manually or by import.
21. User sets price, cost price, quantity, reorder threshold, barcode.
22. User sets opening stock.

## 11.6 Staff Setup
23. User creates cashier.
24. User creates manager.
25. User creates stock officer.
26. User assigns permissions and branch access.

## 11.7 Finance Setup
27. User enables payment methods such as cash, mobile money, and card.
28. User creates expense categories.
29. User sets receipt defaults.
30. User configures finance preferences.

## 11.8 POS Setup
31. User enables POS for a branch.
32. Cashier logs in.
33. Cashier opens register and enters opening cash balance.

## 11.9 First Sale
34. Customer comes to counter.
35. Cashier searches or scans products.
36. Items are added to cart.
37. Payment method is selected.
38. Transaction is completed.
39. Receipt is generated.

## 11.10 Automatic System Effects
40. Stock is reduced.
41. Sale is saved.
42. Cashier activity is recorded.
43. Dashboard updates.
44. Sales reports update.
45. Low stock alerts may trigger.

## 11.11 Ongoing Operations
46. Manager reviews branch performance.
47. Owner reviews dashboard and reports.
48. Stock officer restocks and adjusts items.
49. Finance officer enters expenses.
50. Business continues operating daily.

