## 14. Detailed Module Behavior

## 14.1 Authentication Behavior

### Responsibilities
- create account
- log in user
- verify identity
- reset password
- manage sessions
- protect routes

### Rules
- passwords must be hashed securely
- sessions must be revocable
- sensitive routes require authentication
- role and permission checks happen server-side
- account status can block access

### Edge cases
- expired verification code
- invalid login
- locked account
- suspended business account
- expired session
- concurrent device sessions

---

## 14.2 Business Setup Behavior

### Responsibilities
- define the business identity
- establish the business as a tenant
- configure business-wide defaults

### Must capture
- name
- business type
- contact
- address
- currency
- tax basics
- logo
- receipt branding basics

### Important principle
The business setup information is reused across:
- receipts
- reports
- dashboard branding
- communications
- subscription information

---

## 14.3 Branch Management Behavior

### Responsibilities
- support single or multiple branches
- localize staff, stock, and sales per branch
- make reporting branch-aware

### Branch-level data affects
- branch inventory
- cashier assignment
- expense tracking
- sales filtering
- branch performance reports
- permissions

### Important rule
Most day-to-day operational records should be branch-aware.

---

## 14.4 Onboarding Behavior

### Purpose
Prevent users from signing up and getting lost.

### Checklist example
- account verified
- business profile complete
- branch created
- products added
- opening stock set
- staff added
- finance settings configured
- POS enabled
- first sale completed

### System should
- save progress
- show next best action
- reduce friction
- help the user become live quickly

---

## 14.5 Product Management Behavior

### Product creation supports
- name
- category
- selling price
- cost price
- SKU / barcode
- quantity
- unit
- reorder threshold
- branch linkage where relevant
- optional image
- optional expiry / batch behavior

### Important design principle
Products are not just display data. They influence:
- POS availability
- stock tracking
- profit estimation
- alerts
- category reports
- best seller analysis

### Edge cases
- duplicate SKU
- invalid barcode
- negative price
- disabled products still appearing in POS
- bulk import row errors

---

## 14.6 Inventory Behavior

### Inventory must support
- opening stock
- restock additions
- reductions from sales
- transfers
- adjustments
- damage
- expiry
- physical stock counts

### Core rule
All stock changes should be explainable through movement history.

### Important outputs
- current quantity
- low stock alerts
- out of stock state
- stock valuation
- branch stock views
- movement history

### High-risk area
Inventory errors destroy trust. Stock flows must be deterministic and auditable.

---

## 14.7 Staff and Permissions Behavior

### Staff system must support
- different roles
- branch assignments
- role-based access control
- custom permission overrides
- temporary passwords or invite flows
- deactivation
- activity visibility

### Important rule
Permission enforcement must happen both in UI visibility and backend authorization.

### Examples
- cashier cannot edit finance settings
- stock officer cannot see sensitive financial summaries unless granted
- branch manager cannot access another branch unless allowed
- only authorized roles can refund sales or change pricing

---

## 14.8 POS Behavior

### POS must be:
- fast
- keyboard-friendly where needed
- search-efficient
- barcode-ready
- clear under pressure
- cashier-friendly

### POS actions
- open register
- search products
- scan products
- add to cart
- modify quantity
- apply discount
- attach customer
- choose payment method
- complete sale
- generate receipt
- hold sale
- resume sale
- refund / return if allowed
- close shift

### Automatic system effects after successful sale
- save sale
- save line items
- reduce stock
- update dashboards
- write activity log
- update cashier stats
- possibly trigger low stock alerts

### Risks
- duplicate sale processing
- slow checkout
- stock not updating
- wrong totals
- receipts not generating

---

## 14.9 Sales Behavior

### Sales module must support
- sale record storage
- detailed line item review
- branch filtering
- cashier filtering
- payment method filtering
- refund and void visibility
- exports

### Sale records must preserve
- exact items sold
- quantities
- prices at sale time
- discount state
- payment metadata
- cashier identity
- customer identity if attached
- timestamp
- branch

---

## 14.10 Customer Behavior

### Customer module supports
- customer identity
- contact info
- purchase history
- notes
